subject: HISTORY
text: Give the century, B.C. or A.D., of each of the following, indicate who or what each was, and say why each is important in history. Answers must be written in the space provided after each name: St. Thomas Aquinas, The Massacre of St. Bartholomew's Day, Charles the Bold of Burgundy, Madame Curie, Danton, The Hegira, John Hus, The Athenian Expedition to Sicily, Marshal Turenne, Publius Vergilius Maro (Virgil).
